    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-10-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-10-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="438"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d438">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/926.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Puerto Plata</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Puerto Plata</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-10-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 16, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>All misunderstanding cleared away. The revolutionists have accepted treaty of
                    peace signed in Santo Domingo October 6 [omission in transmission]. Vásquez and
                    Céspedes have signed the original copy and deposited it with me.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hathaway</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
